          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/619.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, roughly tear and crumble both your <strong>flat white</strong> and<strong> chestnut mushrooms</strong> directly into the pan</p><p>Cook over a high heat for 3-5 min or until starting to brown and caramelise – these are your <strong>caramelised mushrooms</strong></p>",
